description: Provides the possibility to see live JMeter metrics (aggregation table, errors, the response body of failures), uses the same mechanics to generate the report with metrics as JMeter.

options.content: The following panels show aggregated metrics for all requests

targets.query: SELECT last("meanActiveThreads") FROM "virtualUsers" WHERE  $timeFilter  GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT  count("responseTime")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter  GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT sum("sentBytes") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT  count("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE ("requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT count("responseTime") as "total" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" =~ /->/ AND "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter
SELECT  count("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE ("errorMessage" = 'Null' and "requestName" =~ /->/ AND "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT  sum("errorCount") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT 1 - sum("errorCount")/count("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE $timeFilter
SELECT sum("errorCount")/count("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  $timeFilter
SELECT  count("responseTime")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT mean("meanActiveThreads")  FROM "virtualUsers" WHERE  $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT count("responseTime")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY "requestName", time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT mean("meanActiveThreads")  FROM "virtualUsers" WHERE  $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT count("count")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE ("errorMessage" = '' AND "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY  time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT count("count")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE ("errorMessage" != '' and  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY  time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT count("count")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY "responseCode", time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT mean("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s), requestName
SELECT percentile(responseTime, 90)/1000 as "90%" FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  $timeFilter GROUP BY requestName
SELECT mean("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE   $timeFilter  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 90) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE   $timeFilter  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 95) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  $timeFilter  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 99) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT max("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE   $timeFilter  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)

SELECT mean( "f1000") *100/$total
FROM
(SELECT count("responseTime") as "f1000" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter AND responseTime <=1000)
GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)

SELECT mean( "f2000") *100/$total
FROM
(SELECT count("responseTime") as "f2000" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter AND responseTime <=1500)
GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)

SELECT mean( "f1000") *100/$total
FROM
(SELECT count("responseTime") as "f1000" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter AND responseTime <=2000)
GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)

SELECT mean( "f1000") *100/$total
FROM
(SELECT count("responseTime") as "f1000" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE   "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter AND responseTime <=3000)
GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)

SELECT mean( "f1000") *100/$total
FROM
(SELECT count("responseTime") as "f1000" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE   "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter AND responseTime >= 5000)
GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)

SELECT count(responseTime) as Count,  mode("responseTime")/1000 as Mode, mean(responseTime)/1000 as Avg,  median(responseTime)/1000 as Median, percentile(responseTime, 90)/1000 as "90%",percentile(responseTime, 95)/1000 as "95%",percentile(responseTime, 99)/1000 as "99%", min(responseTime)/1000 as Min, max(responseTime)/1000 as Max,  stddev(responseTime)/1000 as "Std. Dev",  (sum(errorCount)/count(responseTime)) as "Error Rate" FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY requestName

SELECT count(responseTime) as Count,  mode("responseTime") as Mode, mean(responseTime) as Avg,  median(responseTime) as Median, percentile(responseTime, 90) as "90%",percentile(responseTime, 95) as "95%",percentile(responseTime, 99) as "99%", min(responseTime) as Min, max(responseTime)/1000 as Max,  stddev(responseTime) as "Std. Dev",  (sum(errorCount)/count(responseTime)) as "Error Rate" FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY requestName
SELECT  sum("errorCount") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE ("requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND errorCount !=0 ) AND $timeFilter AND $timeFilter GROUP  BY time([[aggregation]]s), requestName

SELECT  sum("errorCount") AS "Error Count" FROM "autogen"."requestsRaw" WHERE ("requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND "errorCount" !=0 and $timeFilter) GROUP BY  "requestName",  "errorMessage", "responseCode"

SELECT  sum("errorCount") AS "Error Count" FROM "autogen"."requestsRaw" WHERE ( "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND "errorCount" !=0 and $timeFilter) GROUP BY  "requestName",  "errorMessage", "responseCode",  "errorResponseBody"

SELECT  sum("errorCount") AS "Error Count" FROM "autogen"."requestsRaw" WHERE ("requestName" =~ /^$errorRequest$/ AND "errorCount" !=0 AND  "responseCode"=~ /^$responseCode$/ and $timeFilter) GROUP BY  "requestName",  "errorMessage", "responseCode",  "errorResponseBody"
SELECT ELAPSED("count", 1s)  FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  ("requestName" =~ /->/ AND "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s), requestName
SELECT elapsed(mean("responseTime"), 1s) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE ("requestName" =~ /->/ AND "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time(10s), "requestName" fill(null)
SELECT elapsed(mean("count"), 1s) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE ("requestName" =~ /->/ AND "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s), "requestName"
SELECT mean("latency") FROM "autogen"."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s), "requestName"
SELECT mean("sentBytes") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/  AND $timeFilter GROUP  BY time([[aggregation]]s), requestName
SELECT mean("connectTime") FROM "autogen"."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s), "requestName"
SELECT mean("receivedBytes") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/  AND $timeFilter GROUP  BY time([[aggregation]]s), requestName
SELECT mean("sentBytes") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/  AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)
SELECT mean("receivedBytes") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE   "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/  AND $timeFilter GROUP  BY time([[aggregation]]s)
SELECT mean("processingTime") FROM "autogen"."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s), "requestName"
SELECT count("count")/$r_integral as  "Throughput per second" FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  "requestName" =~ /^$request$/   AND $timeFilter GROUP BY  requestName
SELECT (count("count")/$r_integral) *60 as  "Throughput per minute" FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE   "requestName" =~ /^$request$/   AND $timeFilter GROUP BY  requestName
SELECT ((count("count")/$r_integral) *60*60) as  "Throughput per hour" FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  "requestName" =~ /^$request$/  AND $timeFilter GROUP BY  requestName

SELECT count(responseTime) as Count, mean(responseTime)/1000 as Avg,  median(responseTime)/1000 as Median, percentile(responseTime, 90)/1000 as "90%",percentile(responseTime, 95)/1000 as "95%",percentile(responseTime, 99)/1000 as "99%", min(responseTime)/1000 as Min, max(responseTime)/1000 as Max,  stddev(responseTime)/1000 as "Std. Dev", (sum(errorCount)/count(responseTime)) as "Error Rate" FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  ("requestName" =~ /^$request$/  AND $timeFilter) GROUP BY requestName
SELECT count("responseTime")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT mean("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 90) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 95) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 99) FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT max("responseTime") FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT sum("errorCount")/$aggregation FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)

SELECT mean( "f1000") *100/$total_r

FROM

(SELECT count("responseTime") as "f1000" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter AND responseTime <=1000 ) 
,
(SELECT count("responseTime") as "total" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE   "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time(10s) fill(null))

GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)

SELECT mean( "f2000") *100/$total_r

FROM

(SELECT count("responseTime") as "f2000" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter AND responseTime <=2000 ) 
,
(SELECT count("responseTime") as "total" FROM "requestsRaw" WHERE  "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time(10s) fill(null))

GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s)
SELECT count(count) as Count  FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY requestName
SELECT integral(count) as TotalTime FROM "requestsRaw"  WHERE  "requestName" !~ /^SCRIPT/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY requestName
